## Limitations and Scope Boundaries

### Conscious Limitations

**What This Study Includes:**
- Doctrinal analysis of regulatory framework
- Judicial response analysis through case law
- International comparative baseline (UK/Singapore)
- Policy recommendations based on documentary evidence

**What This Study Does Not Include:**
- Empirical data from banks on actual freezing practices
- Stakeholder interviews (bank officials, law enforcement)
- Comprehensive multi-country comparative analysis
- Banking Ombudsman decisions (separate database)
- Consumer court jurisprudence
- Real-time RTI data on freeze frequency

**Rationale for Scope:**
These limitations are acknowledged to maintain feasibility while ensuring rigor in chosen methods. Future research should incorporate empirical components.

